Hal Pomeranz asks "How many commands could we emulate if we only had the shell?"

http://blog.commandlinekungfu.com/2009/09/episode-61-just-sit-right-back-youll.html

This is an echo of Tom Christiansen's "Perl Power Tools" project, which aims to reimplement all classic Unix commands in Perl.
(PPT gives you the Unix commands on any OS that supports Perl, not just Linux and Unix.)

http://alumnus.caltech.edu/~copeland/work/PDF/1999-08-ppt.pdf
